        "content": "<p>This is not a concrete answer but a further specification of your question is- what are some important cases where the tensor and Hom functors fail to be exact and what's the practical impact of that?<br>\nExamples should probably be computational in nature. We want to describe X by generators and relations so we can compute with it but \"characterizing X by generators and relations doesn't play nice with functors that aren't right exact\".</p>",
